./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:1546:my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:20:2. **Memory-tagged, mood-aware selection.** Samples carry rich metadata. The sample-selector matches samples to current artist mode, arc phase, harmonic context, and mood — never random. A sample picked for *Solitary* mode will never appear in *Working ambience* mode unless the metadata aligns.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:1551:my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:48:**Phase 4 — Composer integration (CCS-022..CCS-028).** Mode-driven sampler density (solitary heavy, working light, etc.); `select_sample()` wired into cast/instrument-patch path so the composer treats the sampler as a first-class voice; self-quotation loop captures composer output when arc-payoff is high; keyboard/Theramini capture during human play; per-mode effects-bus presets; operator diagnostics surface currently-active samples. End of phase: pieces start to noticeably *cite themselves* across sessions, and the room's acoustic history becomes audible material.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:1552:my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:50:**Phase 5 — Verification + observability (CCS-029..CCS-033).** Per-piece sampler-event metrics; anti-pattern detection for sampler dominating (over-quote) or never appearing (silent quintet member); a sample-usage journal that records which samples played in which pieces with what transformations; end-to-end smoke test on cypherclaw confirming the daemon is capturing, the selector is choosing, the synth is playing, and the self-listener is observing the right output peaks. End of phase: composer can demonstrate a piece that uses 1 self-quotation + 1 room-capture + 1 library sample, all selector-chosen, all routed through the effects bus, all surfaced in the diagnostics dashboard.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:1559:my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:105:| CCS-017 | Auto-tag captured samples: arc phase, mood, presence, time-of-day, plus heuristic acoustic tags (warm if low spectral centroid, metallic if high+narrow band, transient if high transient density, etc.). | MUST | T1 | - `sample_capture_daemon.py::auto_tag(window, context) -> dict` returns a dict mergeable into `SampleRecord`<br/>- arc_phase / mood / presence pulled from `/tmp/organism_state.json` and `/tmp/room_presence.json`<br/>- character tags derived from heuristics: spectral_centroid<800Hz → "warm"; narrow-band high-centroid → "metallic"; sustained_amplitude_ratio>0.7 → "sustained"; transient_density>3/sec → "percussive"; pitch_confidence>0.7 → "harmonic"; etc.<br/>- tests verify each heuristic against canned fixtures and that the merged record validates against `SampleRecord` schema |
