./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9848:I’ve got the seam now: score-tree sections already carry `sample_gesture_*`, arc-phase, and payoff-focus metadata into tracker scenes, but the usage journal still only persists `samples_played` and a payoff string. I’m checking the changelog/progress conventions and then I’ll write the task spec and the new failing integration test around the real compiled tracker song plus runtime event emission.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9852:# Changelog
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9856:- Added focused regression coverage for the operator-diagnostics sampler line (`OperatorDiagnostics.sample_source`) in `tests/test_operator_diagnostics_sample_status.py`, pinning the four discrete states the formatter must produce: sampling-only renders `currently sampling …` without a playback fragment, playing-only renders `playing sample …` without a sampling fragment, both-active joins the two phrases with ` · `, and the all-idle case degrades to `unavailable` so the daemon never serializes an empty sampler line.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9858:- Wired the combined sampler plan+playback status line into the face display renderer so the small face monitor mirrors operator diagnostics: added `senseweave.sample_status.face_display_sample_status_text(...)` as a thin wrapper that opts into `combine_activity_and_playback=True`, and updated `my-claw/tools/face_display.py` to call it in place of the legacy either/or `sample_status_text(...)` while preserving the existing 24pt centered placement and degradation guards. Coverage in `tests/test_face_display_sample_status.py` pins the combined wording, plan-only fallback, monitor-offline degradation, and the renderer call site.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9859:- Operator `/status` sampler diagnostics now combine sampler plan and active playback into one human-readable line when both `/tmp/sample_dsp_activity.json` and `/tmp/sample_playback_state.json` are present, while leaving the face-display sampler wording on its existing playback-first contract; added regression coverage in `tests/test_operator_diagnostics.py`, `tests/test_sample_status.py`, and `tests/test_musical_integration_runtime.py`.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9860:- Wired active-song human phrase capture into the live listeners: new `senseweave.phrase_capture_runtime.ActiveSongPhraseCapture` gates `PhraseCaptureWriter` on fresh `/tmp/composer_state.json` song context, `midi_keyboard_listener.py` and `theramini_listener.py` now feed qualifying >5s phrases into `samples/keyboard/` and `samples/theramini/` with validated song/key/tempo sidecars, `PhraseCaptureWriter` now exposes `reset()` for safe song-boundary drops, and `human_phrase_capture_verify.py` plus new runtime/integration tests simulate both sources without hardware and validate the resulting paths and tags.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9866:- Added `docs/cypherclaw-sampler-architecture.md` to fill the gap between the sampler PRD and the musicianship roadmap: it lists the landed sampler components (`sample_capture_daemon.py`, `sample_capture_verify.py`, `sampler_buffers.py`, `sampler_dispatch.py`, `synthesis/sampler_effects.scd`, `render/antipatterns.py`), traces the end-to-end signal flow from JACK input through capture, tagging, `index.sqlite`, dispatch, the `sw_sampler_fx` bus, and the master bus, names both live anti-pattern detectors (`sampler_dominating`, `sampler_silent_quintet_member`), enumerates integration seams (identity, cast planner, mix engine, composer, operator diagnostics), and explicitly flags `SampleLibrary`, `SampleSelector`, `sw_sampler.scd`, and quintet identity convergence as still pending; `tests/test_cypherclaw_sampler_architecture.py` pins the doc's required sections, the referenced file paths, and the live anti-pattern names so future renames or section drops force the doc to update with the code.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9867:- Updated `docs/cypherclaw-musicianship-roadmap.md` to describe the active quintet direction: `sw_bell_warm`, `sw_bowed`, `sw_breath`, `sw_pad`, and the new `sw_sampler` memory voice; the roadmap now separates landed sampler modules (`sample_capture_daemon.py`, `sampler_buffers.py`, `sampler_dispatch.py`, `sampler_effects.scd`, anti-pattern checks) from still-pending identity/library/SynthDef convergence so the documentation matches the tree's real partial-rollout state.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9868:- Wired sample auto-tagging into the capture write path: `sample_capture_daemon.py` now exposes a stdlib-only `save_capture()` helper that writes mono 24-bit WAV captures, emits contextual + acoustic tags via `build_sample_tags()`, and persists both flattened tag fields and JSON payloads into `index.sqlite`; `tests/test_sample_capture_daemon.py` now covers room/contextual tag emission, sample-index persistence, and percussive contact-capture indexing.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9871:- Added listener-review workflow: `my-claw/docs/listener-review.md` documents weekly review cadence, step-by-step rule ablation via the `senseweave-render-debugger` CLI (CCH-010), and how to attach review notes; `my-claw/sdp/review-log.md` provides a structured template with piece, date, felt_wrong, suspected_rule, ablation_result, and action fields; `render.listener_review` validates artifact integrity and anchors the documented CLI name to the live debugger parser.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9872:- Added audio-rendered novelty verification for SenseWeave fixtures: `render.audio_novelty` now writes deterministic 5-minute proxy WAVs, extracts librosa mel-feature self-similarity matrices plus Foote novelty curves, aligns symbolic CCH-034 novelty peak times to audio peaks within 500 ms, and fails flattened synthesis even when symbolic metrics remain healthy.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9875:- Added operator diagnostics for production-course decisions: `operator_diagnostics.py` now extracts production-course chapter values (phase, scale/mode, harmonic function, groove, production strategy, mix role, spatial profile) from tracker runtime `scene_metadata` with fallback to score-tree sections; Theramini relation combines counterpoint relation with live Theramini playing state; critique notes derive threshold violations from ear-engine metrics; all three fields degrade gracefully to "unavailable" when authority files are absent or corrupt; `/status` display renders the new fields in the SenseWeave section.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9877:- Added course-driven self-critique and revision targets: `self_critique.py` now maps production-course chapter concepts (mode_scale, harmonic_function, meter_groove, counterpoint_relation, synthesis_architecture, mix_role, spatial_intent, genre_strategy, transition_type, phase_profile) to concrete ear-engine metric thresholds via `COURSE_METRIC_MAP`; `thresholds_for_course()` merges per-section course metadata into quality thresholds (stricter wins); `critique_score_with_course()` returns a `CourseCritiqueReport` with `CourseFailure` attribution naming the specific course concept behind each metric violation; `revision_targets_from_failures()` maps failures to `RevisionTargets` specifying which musical dimensions (form, harmony, rhythm, register, mix, strategy) are open for bounded revision without changing piece identity; `revise_score()` accepts an optional `course` kwarg; `tracker_compiler.py` and `duet_composer.py` fallback paths now pass section production_course to `revise_score`.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9882:- Added artistic identity portfolio reporting and surface snapshots: new `portfolio_report.py` module provides `derive_portfolio_report()` for comprehensive identity summaries from repertoire metrics, preferred forms/modes, motif counts, practice block coverage with EMSD course codes, growth-state keys, and ear quality averages; and `derive_surface_snapshot()` for face/operator display data (current song title, section caption, practice block, artistic-intent line). Graceful degradation handles empty repertoire, missing fields, corrupt score trees, and absent growth state without hallucinating data.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9883:- Added installation-aware acoustic ecology policies: new `acoustic_ecology.py` module provides `resolve_acoustic_ecology()` which translates presence, cadence, day phase, room activity, attention state, and dwell time into a frozen `AcousticEcologyPolicy` with hard ceilings for volume, onset density, and spectral brightness, silence window parameters, ordered source preferences, keynote privilege weights, and density/voice caps. Sleep and wind-down modes enforce non-negotiable ceilings that cannot be overridden by any modifier. Performance attention overrides wind-down constraints when the human is actively engaged. Room activity boosts keynote privilege so the room's own soundscape is the acoustic content.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9885:- Added pre-performance self-critique and bounded revision passes: new `self_critique.py` module provides `preview_score()` for offline metric analysis, `critique_score()` for threshold-based quality gating, and `revise_score()` for one bounded rewrite attempt that preserves piece identity (key, mood, tempo) while improving at least one failed metric.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9888:- Rebalanced the first live score-tree pass for audibility: fresh post-restart commissions now avoid jumping straight to a maximal sparse suite unless the cadence is already wind-down/sleep-oriented, and `music_tracker_runtime.py` now emits stronger safe amplitudes for primary melody/bass/rhythm lanes so a healthy running piece is easier to hear and meter.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9892:- Coordinated those internal phrase families across tracker roles: shared root/function profiles now shape melody, bass, counter, and color variants together, and tracker steps expose `internal_family_root_degree` plus `internal_family_function` for diagnostics and future orchestration consumers.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9902:- Fixed the live score-tree runtime on CypherClaw: `duet_composer.py` now derives commission context defensively from the world when `TrackerPlan` lacks `day_phase` / `weekly_phase`, `master_bus.py` now exposes an explicit `sw_master_smooth` seed helper, and `restart_composer.sh` now reseeds that master node again after the new composer PID is confirmed alive so the first piece does not run with scene-level `/n_set` traffic targeting a dead node.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9906:- Hardened the slow observer-vision path: `observer_vision.py` now treats Ollama `503 server busy / maximum pending requests exceeded` as queue saturation instead of a user-facing description, preserves the HTTP body detail in `vision_error`, emits a compact local fallback description with `vision_backend: \"local_fallback\"`, and backs off before retrying the multimodal model call again.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9916:- Collapsed split boot ownership for the core AV stack: `cypherclaw_boot.sh` now delegates audio/composer/face/gallery/room-listener/sample startup to `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh`, which keeps one authority for those daemons instead of racing duplicate boot paths.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9921:- Relaxed composer restart verification to the real steady-state condition: `restart_composer.sh` now waits for any healthy `duet_composer.py` process instead of only trusting the very first child PID, which avoids false failures during the current live startup race.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9924:- Tightened the cold-boot wrapper to avoid daemon duplication: it now waits for `SuperCollider:out_1` before launching the meter, and it only backfills `room_listener.py`, `sample_playback_engine.py`, and `face_display.py` if another startup source has not already brought them up during the same boot.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9925:- Made the cold-boot wrapper opportunistic instead of combative: if `scsynth` and `duet_composer.py` are already present from another startup path, `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` now skips `start_audio.sh` / `restart_composer.sh` entirely and only backfills the missing meter/listener surface.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9929:- Swapped the self-listener toward a host-stable monitor path: `self_listener.py` now prefers a PipeWire sink monitor target when one is available, still falls back to direct JACK or `pw-jack` port capture when needed, and keeps the old backend cache/reprobe logic only as fallback behavior instead of the primary live path.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9931:- Tightened the display recovery behavior again: `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` now force-restarts `face_display.py` and `gallery_x11.py` on recovery instead of only deduplicating them, because a single stale headless display process was enough to leave the monitors blank while still looking “healthy” in `ps`.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9941:- Adjusted room-listener fallback priority so ALSA auto-selection now prefers the Perform-VE interface over webcam or generic analog capture when JACK is unavailable.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9947:- Expanded CypherClaw boot coverage for the EMSD sampler path: `cypherclaw_boot.sh` now starts `theramini_listener.py` and `contact_listener.py` alongside the room listener so the stable sample aliases can refresh during unattended startup instead of remaining planned-but-missing files.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9949:- Wired the next EMSD runtime pass into live state: added `emsd_runtime.py`, taught `duet_composer.py` to build a typed EMSD context per tracker song and publish arc/mix/sample/DSP/identity fields into `/tmp/composer_state.json`, extended `repertoire_memory.py` to retain `patch_name`, and taught `self_listener.py` to publish `/tmp/glyph_audio_features.json` by combining live audio analysis with composer/cadence state for GlyphWeave-facing consumers.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9950:- Built the first end-to-end EMSD package: added a 40-course curriculum catalog plus generated `my-claw/curriculum/EMSD-*` scaffolds, and implemented `sound_palette_lab.py`, `sample_lab.py`, `mix_engine.py`, `procedural_arc.py`, `dsp_scene_lab.py`, `artistic_identity.py`, and `capstone_engine.py` so the electronic music production roadmap now exists as runnable code and tests instead of only a brief.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9959:- Made repertoire answer hooks less literal and less repetitive: `hook_engine.py` now chooses among contextual phrase-level answer variants based on family/cadence/song state, so recalled hook lines stay grammatical without collapsing into one stock response.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9969:- Added family-level motif memory to the live tracker path: `ContinuousLearner` now tags songs with tracker family, progression profile, cadence state, and patch context, `MelodicMemory` can retrieve matching fragments by keyword, and `score_from_mood()` now prefers and answers same-family/profile motifs instead of drawing only from a generic recent fragment pool.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9985:- Added SenseWeave operator diagnostics to daemon `/status`, including score tree, section function, arrangement curve, ear metrics, sample source, master bus, self-listener, and independent rollout flags for curriculum/exercise, preview render, self-critique, and long-form suites.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9991:- Added a Telegram `/local` built-in backed by a shared daemon status snapshot so operators can request per-socket Ollama health, loaded models, and latency on demand.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9992:- Wired `ollama_health()` into the `/status` Telegram command and half-hour heartbeat so operators can see per-socket Ollama health, loaded models, and latency without SSH.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9993:- Added daemon-local `ollama_health()` dual-socket reporting for ports `11434` and `11435`, including per-instance loaded models and measured probe latency.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:10002:- Taught Telegram `/prd` to load stage order from `sdp/execution-roadmap.md` and batch mappings from `sdp/execution-roadmap.queue-map.json`, so roadmap output follows the current clone/identity/embodiment/publication plan instead of a stale hardcoded stage list.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:10007:- Expanded Telegram `/monitor` with compact `sdp-cli`-style status lines for completion gate, latest completed run verdict/pair, and live per-agent quota/provider health.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:10013:- Added the missing `OPT-005` half-hour Telegram heartbeat in the live daemon scheduler, including uptime, I/O wait, memory, load, available-agent count, queue progress, pet XP summary, and Observatory logging.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:10019:- Unified `promptclaw doctor` with optional runtime preflight so live CypherClaw roots report config health and runtime readiness through one entry point.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:10020:- Hardened the CypherClaw Telegram helper so bot token and chat ID must come from environment instead of hardcoded defaults.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:10035:- Added decision context and constitutional rules injection into agent prompts.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:10042:- Updated prompt_builder.py with `coherence_context` parameter on all build functions.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:10050:- Added an interactive startup wizard that asks onboarding questions one at a time.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:10051:- Added heuristic follow-up questions when startup answers are vague or underspecified.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:10053:- Added startup artifacts: `docs/STARTUP_PROFILE.md`, `docs/STARTUP_TRANSCRIPT.md`, and `.promptclaw/onboarding/startup-session.md`.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:10054:- Added agent roster customization and capability inference during startup.
