./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:25992:# Changelog
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:25996:- Added focused regression coverage for the operator-diagnostics sampler line (`OperatorDiagnostics.sample_source`) in `tests/test_operator_diagnostics_sample_status.py`, pinning the four discrete states the formatter must produce: sampling-only renders `currently sampling …` without a playback fragment, playing-only renders `playing sample …` without a sampling fragment, both-active joins the two phrases with ` · `, and the all-idle case degrades to `unavailable` so the daemon never serializes an empty sampler line.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:25998:- Wired the combined sampler plan+playback status line into the face display renderer so the small face monitor mirrors operator diagnostics: added `senseweave.sample_status.face_display_sample_status_text(...)` as a thin wrapper that opts into `combine_activity_and_playback=True`, and updated `my-claw/tools/face_display.py` to call it in place of the legacy either/or `sample_status_text(...)` while preserving the existing 24pt centered placement and degradation guards. Coverage in `tests/test_face_display_sample_status.py` pins the combined wording, plan-only fallback, monitor-offline degradation, and the renderer call site.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:25999:- Operator `/status` sampler diagnostics now combine sampler plan and active playback into one human-readable line when both `/tmp/sample_dsp_activity.json` and `/tmp/sample_playback_state.json` are present, while leaving the face-display sampler wording on its existing playback-first contract; added regression coverage in `tests/test_operator_diagnostics.py`, `tests/test_sample_status.py`, and `tests/test_musical_integration_runtime.py`.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:26000:- Wired active-song human phrase capture into the live listeners: new `senseweave.phrase_capture_runtime.ActiveSongPhraseCapture` gates `PhraseCaptureWriter` on fresh `/tmp/composer_state.json` song context, `midi_keyboard_listener.py` and `theramini_listener.py` now feed qualifying >5s phrases into `samples/keyboard/` and `samples/theramini/` with validated song/key/tempo sidecars, `PhraseCaptureWriter` now exposes `reset()` for safe song-boundary drops, and `human_phrase_capture_verify.py` plus new runtime/integration tests simulate both sources without hardware and validate the resulting paths and tags.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:26006:- Added `docs/cypherclaw-sampler-architecture.md` to fill the gap between the sampler PRD and the musicianship roadmap: it lists the landed sampler components (`sample_capture_daemon.py`, `sample_capture_verify.py`, `sampler_buffers.py`, `sampler_dispatch.py`, `synthesis/sampler_effects.scd`, `render/antipatterns.py`), traces the end-to-end signal flow from JACK input through capture, tagging, `index.sqlite`, dispatch, the `sw_sampler_fx` bus, and the master bus, names both live anti-pattern detectors (`sampler_dominating`, `sampler_silent_quintet_member`), enumerates integration seams (identity, cast planner, mix engine, composer, operator diagnostics), and explicitly flags `SampleLibrary`, `SampleSelector`, `sw_sampler.scd`, and quintet identity convergence as still pending; `tests/test_cypherclaw_sampler_architecture.py` pins the doc's required sections, the referenced file paths, and the live anti-pattern names so future renames or section drops force the doc to update with the code.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:26007:- Updated `docs/cypherclaw-musicianship-roadmap.md` to describe the active quintet direction: `sw_bell_warm`, `sw_bowed`, `sw_breath`, `sw_pad`, and the new `sw_sampler` memory voice; the roadmap now separates landed sampler modules (`sample_capture_daemon.py`, `sampler_buffers.py`, `sampler_dispatch.py`, `sampler_effects.scd`, anti-pattern checks) from still-pending identity/library/SynthDef convergence so the documentation matches the tree's real partial-rollout state.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:26008:- Wired sample auto-tagging into the capture write path: `sample_capture_daemon.py` now exposes a stdlib-only `save_capture()` helper that writes mono 24-bit WAV captures, emits contextual + acoustic tags via `build_sample_tags()`, and persists both flattened tag fields and JSON payloads into `index.sqlite`; `tests/test_sample_capture_daemon.py` now covers room/contextual tag emission, sample-index persistence, and percussive contact-capture indexing.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:26011:- Added listener-review workflow: `my-claw/docs/listener-review.md` documents weekly review cadence, step-by-step rule ablation via the `senseweave-render-debugger` CLI (CCH-010), and how to attach review notes; `my-claw/sdp/review-log.md` provides a structured template with piece, date, felt_wrong, suspected_rule, ablation_result, and action fields; `render.listener_review` validates artifact integrity and anchors the documented CLI name to the live debugger parser.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:26012:- Added audio-rendered novelty verification for SenseWeave fixtures: `render.audio_novelty` now writes deterministic 5-minute proxy WAVs, extracts librosa mel-feature self-similarity matrices plus Foote novelty curves, aligns symbolic CCH-034 novelty peak times to audio peaks within 500 ms, and fails flattened synthesis even when symbolic metrics remain healthy.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:26015:- Added operator diagnostics for production-course decisions: `operator_diagnostics.py` now extracts production-course chapter values (phase, scale/mode, harmonic function, groove, production strategy, mix role, spatial profile) from tracker runtime `scene_metadata` with fallback to score-tree sections; Theramini relation combines counterpoint relation with live Theramini playing state; critique notes derive threshold violations from ear-engine metrics; all three fields degrade gracefully to "unavailable" when authority files are absent or corrupt; `/status` display renders the new fields in the SenseWeave section.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:26024: - **Details:** Full validation passed (`pip install -e '.[dev]'`, `pytest tests/ -x`, `ruff check src/ tests/`, `mypy src/`). The recurring hardening anchors were also rechecked explicitly without broadening scope: `tests/test_self_critique.py::TestPipelineIntegration::{test_tracker_compiler_uses_revise_score,test_fallback_path_uses_revise_score}` passed for self-critique wiring, `tests/test_resource_governor.py` passed for budget enforcement, and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` passed for `bootstrap_identity()` ordering.
