./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:35801: - Added focused regression coverage for the operator-diagnostics sampler line (`OperatorDiagnostics.sample_source`) in `tests/test_operator_diagnostics_sample_status.py`, pinning the four discrete states the formatter must produce: sampling-only renders `currently sampling …` without a playback fragment, playing-only renders `playing sample …` without a sampling fragment, both-active joins the two phrases with ` · `, and the all-idle case degrades to `unavailable` so the daemon never serializes an empty sampler line.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:35803: - Wired the combined sampler plan+playback status line into the face display renderer so the small face monitor mirrors operator diagnostics: added `senseweave.sample_status.face_display_sample_status_text(...)` as a thin wrapper that opts into `combine_activity_and_playback=True`, and updated `my-claw/tools/face_display.py` to call it in place of the legacy either/or `sample_status_text(...)` while preserving the existing 24pt centered placement and degradation guards. Coverage in `tests/test_face_display_sample_status.py` pins the combined wording, plan-only fallback, monitor-offline degradation, and the renderer call site.
