./sdp/logs/Lead_frac-0113_1777794485.log:1742:sdp/verification/t-001@20260425t183959zd-verify.md:18:**`evict_lru()` delegation**: The new public `evict_lru()` peeks at the oldest entry with `next(iter(self._lru.items()))` (no mutation), then delegates to `on_sampler_free(oldest)` which sends `/b_free`, clears `buffer_id`, and removes the record from `_lru` via `pop`. The method returns the evicted record (or `None` on empty). This fully routes eviction through the free path — no duplicated release logic remains.
