sdp/verification/t-022@20260425t183959zc-verify.md:82:{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-04-26T04:46:01.807Z","tool_name":"write_file","tool_id":"write_file_1777178761807_0","parameters":{"content":"# Verification Report — T-022@20260425T183959Zc\n\n**Verify Agent:** Gemini CLI\n**Date:** 2026-04-26\n**Artifacts Reviewed:**\n- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/usage_journal.py`\n- `tests/test_usage_journal.py`\n- `my-claw/tools/daemon.py`\n- `my-claw/tools/cypherclaw_daemon.py`\n- `tests/test_first_boot.py`\n\n## Correctness\nThe implementation correctly wires the `post_piece_hook` as requested. It consumes the `SampleUsageTracker` state, derives a textual arc-payoff summary based on the provided score and sample count, and appends a `JournalEntry` to the storage file. The textual summary banding logic (weak/moderate/strong) is correctly implemented and formatted.\n\n## Completeness\nThe implementation handles all required scenarios:\n- Textual summary rendering with score and count.\n- Hook invocation that correctly resets the tracker state.\n- Durability via `os.fsync` in `append_to_journal` (which was pre-existing but utilized here).\n- Multi-piece append behavior.\n- Error handling when no active piece is tracked (raises `RuntimeError`).\nComprehensive tests cover all these paths.\n\n## Consistency\nThe code follows established patterns in the `usage_journal` module and matches the `JournalEntry` and `SampleUsageTracker` abstractions landed in previous subtasks (Za/Zb). The use of `Path` objects and type hints is consistent with the project's standards.\n\n## Security\nNo security vulnerabilities were identified. The journal storage uses a configurable path that defaults to `samples/usage_journal.jsonl`. No sensitive information is logged or stored.\n\n## Quality\nThe code is clean, modular, and well-tested. The `derive_arc_payoff_summary` function is properly isolated and tested. The hook function is documented and returns the created entry for easy inspection/logging by callers.\n\n## Issues Found\n- [x] (Resolved) Mandatory hardening checks for `bootstrap_identity` were verified as pre-existing and correctly wired in the daemon startup flow.\n\n## Verdict: PASS\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\nThe implementation is solid and satisfies all requirements for T-022 Zc. The integration with the existing tracker and journal persistence layers is seamless. The hardening anchors for startup identity were also verified as passing.\n","file_path":"sdp/verification/t-022 @20260425t183959zc-verify.md"}}
