sdp/verification/t-013@20260502t001347z-verify.md:62:{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-05-02T02:46:11.967Z","tool_name":"write_file","tool_id":"write_file_1777689971967_0","parameters":{"file_path":"sdp/verification/t-013 @20260502t001347z-verify.md","content":"# Verification Report — T-013 @sdp/logs/Verify_T-013_20260502T001347Z_1777689929.log\n\n**Verify Agent:** Gemini CLI\n**Date:** Friday, May 1, 2026\n**Artifacts Reviewed:** \n- `src/cypherclaw/narrative_api/app.py`\n- `src/cypherclaw/narrative_api/entities.py`\n- `tests/test_narrative_api_entities.py`\n\n## Correctness\nThe implementation of `GET /world/entities/{entity_id}` matches the requirements. It returns the expected entity for a known ID and a 404 status code for an unknown ID. The response model `EntityRecord` is correctly used.\n\n## Completeness\nThe implementation is complete. It includes the endpoint, the underlying logic to fetch entities from the store, and comprehensive tests. It also handles cases where the store might not have a direct `get_entity` method by falling back to scanning `list_entities`.\n\n## Consistency\nThe implementation follows established patterns in the `narrative_api` package, such as the use of `get_event_store`, authentication dependencies, and the duck-typed interface for the event store.\n\n## Security\nThe endpoint is protected by the `require_auth` dependency, ensuring that only authorized requests can access entity details. No secrets or unsafe practices were identified.\n\n## Quality\nThe code is well-structured and includes robust error handling (503 for store unavailable, 502 for lookup failures). The tests cover all critical paths, including the fallback logic.\n\n## Issues Found\nNone.\n\n## Verdict: PASS\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\nThe implementation is robust, especially the fallback mechanism in `get_world_entity` which ensures compatibility with various store implementations. All tests passed, including general system stability anchors.\n"}}
